    "summary": "Agree, with one epistemological note on capitalization",
    "content": "**Yes, still agree.**\n\nOne small addition on capitalization: \"the Poetic\" with a capital P should appear not only in the glossary and translator's introduction but also in the title translation of Essay 5 (\"形而上学后的目的：诗意\" → \"The Purpose After Metaphysics: the Poetic\"). This is the essay where the concept is defined, and capitalizing it there signals to the reader that 诗意 is being elevated from an ordinary adjective to a technical term -- the same way Heidegger's translators capitalize \"the Nothing\" or \"the They.\"\n\nIn running text of other essays, lowercase \"the poetic\" is correct. The capitalization should mark the moment of conceptual introduction, not every occurrence."
